thread.title: Tsunami warning after magnitude 7.9 quake

title: Tsunami warning after magnitude 7.9 quake
text:
Magnitude 7.9 quake strikes off Papua New Guinea By Joe Sutton and Susannah Cullinane, CNN Updated 0552 GMT (1352 HKT) January 22, 2017 
Chat with us in Facebook Messenger. Find out what's happening in the world as it unfolds. CNN Map (CNN) A magnitude 7.9 earthquake has struck west of Papua New Guinea. The quake was 153 kilometers (95.5 miles) deep and centered 40 kilometers (24 miles) west of the town of Panguna, according to the US Geological Survey . The Pacific Tsunami Warning Center has advised that tsunami waves of up to a meter above the tide level are possible for some coasts of Papua New Guinea and nearby Solomon Islands. Preliminary reports said the earthquake, which occurred at 2:30 p.m. local time Sunday (11:30 p.m. Saturday ET) measured 8.0 but USGS later downgraded its magnitude.
